bles users to adopt a zero trust application networking model while providing flexible traffic management and observability capabilities.  Kuma also supports a wide variety of platforms including Kubernetes, Nomad, Docker, and Virtual Machines. Thereby allowing organizations to take advantage of these benefits even at the start of their digital transformation journey.","integrations":"Flagger","personas":["SREs","DevOps","Platform Engineers","Architects","Developers"],"release_rate":"Every 8-10 weeks","tags":["mTLS","security","traffic management","observability","microservices","resilience","load balancing","service mesh","policy","wasm","zero trust","multi-cluster","cross-platform","kubernetes","virtual machines"],"use_case":"Kuma is a service mesh that combines the extensibility and performance of Envoy proxy with great UX and a powerful, yet flexible set of policies. It was built from the ground up to support Kubernetes, Docker, and VM environments seamlessly in a single deployment."},"tag":["network"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/KumaMesh"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://linkerd.io/","id":"orchestration-management--service-mesh--linkerd","logo":"logos/f1940543e59719e7ce1929d7bf6004b9fc56db3a6a59a2dc6f0db16c789b28ac.svg","name":"Linkerd","subcategory":"Service Mesh","website":"https://linkerd.io/","accepted_at":"2017-01-23","artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/blob/master/examples/graduated.md#linkerd-logos","audits":[{"date":"2019-06-01","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/linkerd/linkerd2/blob/main/audits/2019/SECURITY_AUDIT.pdf","vendor":"Cure53"},{"date":"2020-06-05","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/ctz/rustls/blob/main/audit/TLS-01-report.pdf","vendor":"Cure53"},{"date":"2022-06-28","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/linkerd/linkerd2/tree/main/audits/2022","vendor":"Trail of Bits"}],"blog_url":"https://blog.linkerd.io/","clomonitor_name":"linkerd","crunchbase_url":"https://www.cru